in... in that dance scene.

49:05.183 --> 49:08.395
Oh, look at that.
Look at that. Stunned.

49:08.478 --> 49:10.397
Lucky man. Lucky man.

49:10.480 --> 49:13.692
Emma and I have always
loved each other, really.

49:13.775 --> 49:16.570
I walked into the room
where we were having tutoring.

49:16.653 --> 49:18.196
<i>The assignment
that had been given</i>

49:18.280 --> 49:21.616
<i>was to draw what you
thought God looked like.</i>

49:21.700 --> 49:26.663
And Tom had drawn a girl with
a backward cap on a skateboard.

49:26.746 --> 49:29.207
<i>And I just don't know
how to say it...</i>

49:29.291 --> 49:31.126
<i>I just fell in love with him.</i>

49:31.209 --> 49:33.920
I think I was in the hair
and makeup chair.

49:34.004 --> 49:36.256
And someone said something
along the lines of,

49:36.339 --> 49:37.465
"Yeah, she had a crush on you."

49:37.549 --> 49:39.009
I used to come in every day

49:39.092 --> 49:40.760
and look for his number
on the call sheet.

49:40.844 --> 49:42.304
It was number seven.

49:42.387 --> 49:44.472
And if it... if... if his number
was on the call sheet,

49:44.556 --> 49:47.100
it was an extra exciting day.

49:47.183 --> 49:49.269
He was three years above me.

49:49.352 --> 49:53.189
And so for him, he was like,
"You're like my little sister."

49:53.273 --> 49:55.358
<i>I was... became very
protective over her.</i>

49:55.442 --> 49:58.028
Yeah, I've always had
a soft spot for... for her,

49:58.111 --> 50:01.072
um, and that continues
to the day.

50:01.156 --> 50:03.950
I think really the truth
of it was Tom

50:04.034 --> 50:09.039
was the one that I could often
be more vulnerable with.

50:09.122 --> 50:10.707
There's always been something
that's like,

50:10.790 --> 50:12.208
I don't know, a kinship.

50:12.292 --> 50:14.628
Nothing has ever, ever, ever,
ever happened

50:14.711 --> 50:16.171
<i>romantically with us.</i>

50:16.254 --> 50:18.632
We just love each other.

50:18.715 --> 50:20.467
That's all I can say
about that.

50:25.889 --> 50:27.807
Together! One...

50:27.891 --> 50:29.392
Two, three.

50:35.941 --> 50:40.153
In "The Goblet of Fire,"
the universe shifts,

50:40.236 --> 50:43.823
and suddenly,
there is Voldemort.

50:50.622 --> 50:53.083
<i>I cast Ralph Fiennes because</i>

50:53.166 --> 50:56.628
<i>he's one of the most potent
actors of his generation.</i>

50:56.711 --> 50:59.589
And I knew
that he had a great force,

50:59.673 --> 51:04.344
<i>just kind of delicate,
subtle force of personality.</i>

51:04.427 --> 51:07.639
<i>My sister has children
who were then</i>

51:07.722 --> 51:09.516
<i>around 10, 11, 12.</i>

51:09.599 --> 51:12.102
I said, "Martha, I don't know
about this Harry Potter thing.

51:12.185 --> 51:14.145
Voldemort. What's that?"

51:14.229 --> 51:15.438
"What?

51:15.522 --> 51:17.649
"You're being asked
to play Voldemort?

51:17.732 --> 51:19.693
You've got to do it!"

51:25.240 --> 51:27.450
<i>And then I was shown
some drawings...</i>

51:27.534 --> 51:28.910
design ideas for the look.

51:28.994 --> 51:31.037
<i>I wasn't expecting that.</i>

51:31.121 --> 51:34.165
<i>And I thought,
"Wow, that's a strong look."</i>

51:34.249 --> 51:36.543
I didn't feel Voldemort
was that human.

51:36.626 --> 51:38.795
I felt he was
the essence of evil.

51:38.878 --> 51:40.213
<i>I know he's been human,</i>

51:40.296 --> 51:42.924
<i>but he's become
a snakelike thing.</i>

51:43.008 --> 51:44.259
So there was the voice.

51:44.342 --> 51:46.928
The sort of snakelike
whispered, husky,

51:47.012 --> 51:51.349
something that I suppose I've...
sort of whispering voice.

51:51.433 --> 51:54.310
Breath on the breath.

51:54.394 --> 51:57.147
"Ah, Harry Potter..."

51:57.230 --> 51:59.357
Come to die.

51:59.441 --> 52:02.652
Ralph wanted to be
ultimately evil

52:02.736 --> 52:03.820
and otherworldly.

52:03.903 --> 52:06.156
<i>And the best way to do that</i>

52:06.239 --> 52:08.575
<i>was to take his nose off.</i>

52:08.658 --> 52:10.910
He does have a nose...
spoiler alert...

52:10.994 --> 52:12.787
<i>and he was covered
in stickers.</i>

52:12.871 --> 52:16.875
So he was slightly less
intimidating than on-screen,

52:16.958 --> 52:18.668
except when they called action.

52:18.752 --> 52:20.754
And for some reason,
I was terrified of him.

52:20.837 --> 52:24.507
I can touch you.

52:24.591 --> 52:26.426
<i>It took about three hours
in makeup,</i>

52:26.509 --> 52:28.636
<i>the painting of the hands,
the nails, the teeth,</i>

52:28.720 --> 52:31.264
and even with my nose,

52:31.347 --> 52:35.894
um, I... I felt...

52:37.771 --> 52:41.274
<i>Strong. It felt powerful.
It felt evil.</i>

52:41.357 --> 52:46.863
What was big was that one
of the people that you assume

52:46.946 --> 52:51.409
is gonna be very important
to the story is Cedric Diggory.

52:51.493 --> 52:56.247
<i>In that confrontation,
Cedric is killed.</i>

52:56.331 --> 52:58.291
Kill the spare.

52:58.374 --> 53:00.835
- <i>Avada Kedavra!</i>
- Cedric!

53:02.462 --> 53:07.759
<i>And Harry,
he manages to take the body</i>

53:07.842 --> 53:12.180
and crash land back at the end
of the competition,

53:12.263 --> 53:16.392
<i>and Cedric Diggory's father
believes that his son has won</i>

53:16.476 --> 53:19.354
and then he realizes
that the kid is dead,

53:19.437 --> 53:21.689
and he howls like a dog.

53:21.773 --> 53:23.149
That's my boy!

53:25.902 --> 53:28.822
That's my boy!

53:28.905 --> 53:31.866
<i>Suddenly, something
completely unexpected</i>

53:31.950 --> 53:34.452
<i>and serious happens,</i>

53:34.536 --> 53:38.164
and suddenly you realize that
this movie is not about life.

53:38.248 --> 53:39.374
It's about death.

53:39.457 --> 53:40.834
<i>It's such a massive scene</i>

53:40.917 --> 53:42.418
<i>'cause it is also
the first time</i>

53:42.502 --> 53:45.421
<i>Harry sort of feels
that kind of death</i>

53:45.505 --> 53:47.549
of... of somebody young,
close to him.

53:48.633 --> 53:50.844
<i>That's a scene I remember
really distinctly going,</i>

53:50.927 --> 53:52.679
<i>"Oh, this is...
yes, these are kids' films,</i>

53:52.762 --> 53:54.514
<i>but my God, there's some
challenging stuff in there."</i>

53:54.597 --> 53:59.018
He's back, he's back.
Voldemort's back.

53:59.102 --> 54:01.271
<i>The moment of
Cedric Diggory's death</i>

54:01.354 --> 54:05.817
<i>is the moment
when the series comes of age,</i>

54:05.900 --> 54:10.071
and now the children
have left childhood

54:10.155 --> 54:12.282
<i>and are going to have
to confront</i>

54:12.365 --> 54:14.617
<i>the perils of adulthood.</i>

54:14.701 --> 54:17.871
<i>And it all comes
from that moment of death.</i>

54:17.954 --> 54:20.707
Cedric Diggory was murdered

54:20.790 --> 54:22.542
by Lord Voldemort.

54:24.335 --> 54:27.005
<i>The three of them,
they're in adversity,</i>

54:27.088 --> 54:30.550
and that forges friendships,
as we know.

54:38.266 --> 54:40.685
<i>"You are protected,
in short,</i>

54:40.768 --> 54:43.188
<i>by your ability to love,"</i>

54:43.271 --> 54:45.690
<i>said Dumbledore loudly.</i>

54:45.773 --> 54:48.526
<i>"The only protection
that can possibly work</i>

54:48.610 --> 54:52.238
<i>"against the lure of power
like Voldemort's.</i>

54:52.322 --> 54:54.532
<i>"In spite
of all the temptation</i>

54:54.616 --> 54:58.036
<i>"you have endured,
all the suffering,</i>

54:58.119 --> 55:01.372
<i>you remain pure of heart."</i>

55:15.345 --> 55:17.764
How nice of you to let us
do this in your house.

55:17.847 --> 55:19.891
I know, so nice.

55:19.974 --> 55:21.392
You know what
I've always wanted to do?

55:21.476 --> 55:24.520
Let me see if we can...
is get up here.

55:25.980 --> 55:28.358
Oh, now, look, they really
don't look very well.

55:29.984 --> 55:32.278
- They're all still here.
- They're really still here.

55:32.362 --> 55:35.782
I mean, has anyone fed them?
This is so sad.

55:35.865 --> 55:37.533
Okay, now you can be
Harry Potter.

55:37.617 --> 55:38.826
Okay, actually.

55:40.745 --> 55:42.622
I'll go down the right,
you go down the left.

55:42.705 --> 55:45.375
Yeah, and let's race, okay?
On your mark, set, go.

55:45.458 --> 55:46.751
Oh, God.

55:47.877 --> 55:49.420
We're snogging down here.

55:50.713 --> 55:52.382
- Get over it.
- You know what?

55:52.465 --> 55:54.634
I-I took a photograph
of something.

55:54.717 --> 55:57.971
Last night, I thought, I'm just
gonna dig up these things,

55:58.054 --> 56:00.056
